<DOC><DOCNO> AP890406-0172 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-06-89 2332EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Germany-Truck     04-06 0152</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Germany-Truck,0157</SECOND><HEAD>U.S. Army Missile Truck Hits House After Brakes Fail</HEAD><DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A U.S. Army truck carrying threeunarmed Hawk missiles crashed into a house on Thursday when thevehicle's brakes failed, but no one was hurt, a military spokesmansaid.   Maj. David Hartman, spokesman for the 32nd Army Air DefenseCommand in Darmstadt, said the crash occurred outside the ruraltown of Weilerbach, about 55 miles southwest of Frankfurt, as thetruck was returning from a field exercise.   He said the missiles were undamaged and the missile transporter,a lengthened model of a 2{-ton truck, was towed to its home basenear Kaiserslautern.   Hawks are ground-to-air rockets designed to carry a conventionalhigh-explosive warhead.   The accident could set off new protests from West German peaceactivists who complain that some ground and air maneuvers by NATOforces based in West Germany put civilian lives at risk.</TEXT></DOC>